title: Rank your own college football top 25!
text:
MORE
Michigan State remains unbeaten through 8 games -- yet still finds itself outside the Top 4 that, if the season ended today, would go to the College Football Playoff.
Jeff Seidel's AP ballot Meanwhile, Michigan remains status quo after a bye week, at No. 17 in the coaches' poll.
Is this where both teams should be ranked? Or do you have a better idea of where they should be? This is where you come in. Submit your ballot below for this week's Freep Reader Poll!
Disclaimer No. 1: Unfortunately, the voting mechanism isn't currently working on mobile devices.
Disclaimer No. 2: If your drag-and-drop isn't working, try refreshing the page. That should fix it.
